ISLAMABAD, Feb 13 (APP): Senate of Pakistan will resume its scheduled business on Monday at 3:00 pm after a two-day break.
According to the agenda shared on the website of the Senate, the House will take up motions, legislative business, the introduction of bills, and further discussion on the recent incident of heckling of a Muslim girl wearing a Hijab by RSS backed mob in the Indian State of Karnataka.
